<p>Hi Emil,</p>
<p>Visit your <a href="https://access.mymind.com/account" style="color: #FF5924;">account settings</a> on desktop and you'll find a new toggle:</p>
<p><strong>✦ Minimalist Mode ✦</strong></p>
<p>When active, it hides the titles for certain cards (images, books, albums etc.) on the main grid, making your mind more streamlined and clean.</p>
<img src="https://carbon-media.accelerator.net/00000000001/epKCygtfoxodjzgoYqEtWC;1000x_.png?auto=webp" width="960" height="463" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;"/>
<p>Titles are still displayed for cards like notes or websites, because they help identify the card itself.</p>
<p>But for many other cards where titles might be redundant, you can how hide them on your grid for a cleaner aesthetic ♡</p>
<p><a href="https://access.mymind.com/everything" style="display: block;width: 289px;border-radius: 25px;background-color:#FF5924;margin:40px auto;padding:8px 13px;color:#fff;font-size:.9em;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-align:center;">OPEN YOUR MIND</a></p>


